			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I wish to speak of what I call RvR Courtesy.  Yesterday my 34 thane was in the hibernia frontier getting some quiet solo xp (beetles, luchs, etc).  Moments after I finish a fight with a beetle, before I can even pick up the loot that dropped, a swarm (30+) of hibernian players decends upon me and slaughters me.  I understand the whole point of RvR, the realms are at war, hibs/albs are the enemy, etc.  However, I am sure I was grey to them as the 1 lurikeen I had targeted was purple to me.  Was the few realm points worth the bubble of xp I lost?  Did it make them feel good they can kill someone 10+ levels lower than them?
<br />

<br />
I know some would say that maybe they thought I was bait, with some shadowblades hiding nearby.  This is why I go away from keeps and stay out in the wide open.  It was plainly obvious that I wasn't doing any RvR, simply was getting some xp for myself.  A few weeks ago a few albs came by BUT didn't just outright slaughter me.  They waved, cheered when I won a fight and were generally polite and mature about the encounter.
<br />

<br />
So I wish to say next time you go out defending your realm, be a little more aware of who you are killing.  Know who is a threat and who isn't.  Know who is out RvRing and who is getting xp.  I know that someday I will be out there fighting for midgard like the rest of them, but at that time just wanted to beat on some beetles.
<br />

<br />
Be safe!   <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
