			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When you are killed in RvR, it's almost the same as being killed by any ordinary mob. You lose no experience or constitution, although you still get rez sickness.
<br />

<br />
It may seem impolite to you, to get killed, but saying that they were all purple because the one you targetted was doesn't make sense. You're admitting that you only targetted one of them. Unless you see epic armour, there's really no way to tell what level they are.
<br />

<br />
As for etiquette, there really isn't much. The frontiers are a great place to level up at certain times, but with all the money and experience you're gaining, there is the threat of being killed by enemy players. One way to minimize this is to play in your own frontier. Yes, you may have had no intention of performing RvR, but you are in an enemies territory. If you want a safer experience, say in your own realm's frontier, or stay in your homeland all-together.
<br />

<br />
Mordred/Andred is an interesting experience, but hopefully Mythic will fix it (no con loss for PvP deaths).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
