				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">To Agravane... if you were in battle and took damage from an NPC monster, then a Player kills you, you DO lost experience.  That is what he is complaining about.
<br />

<br />
Once, I was on my mentalist in the Battleground.  I was level 35.  A Healer was at about 40% health and running away from a goblin.  He would have been one really, really easy kill.  Instead, I mezed the goblin and followed him.  He healed himself up, and then attacked me! He lost, in the end... but I gave him the chance to a fight without an exp loss.
<br />

<br />
I have been exp hunting in the frontier.  There is some great exp to be had out there.  There was this one skald named Osk... grrr.  He killed me several times.  But everytime, he waited for me to A) Finish my battle or B) he finished the battle for me.  I have never lost experience because of him, and I respect him for it.
<br />

<br />
Then again... I have been in the frontier, exp hunting... and have a stealther (normally an archer of somekind) wait for us to pull, THEN attack.  Probably to add to the confusion and to grief.  It sucks to lost exp, but it happens.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
