			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually at one time if you were damaged at all by a realm combatant (Guard or other player) you would lose no experience.
<br />

<br />
It was then discovered that if you chose your hunting area close to patrol routes or near an enemy keep you could avoid PvE experience deaths rather easily.
<br />

<br />
If you got a bad pull all you had to do is run to the nearest enemy guard and suicide.  No experience loss.
<br />

<br />
Now the code is a little more complicated.  It seems if the mob does most of the damage or gets the killing blow you get an XP death.
<br />

<br />
I was a puller in a full group at the Ellyls once and as soon as I pulled (two reds), a stealther put an arrow in my backside <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="icon_eek.gif" border="0" /> .  Our cleric ended up making it to the safety of a keep.  Of the 7 of us that died, 4 were realm deaths and 3 were PvE deaths.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
