			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was teaching my wife how to play and brought her out to the Frontier in the Upplands. I was playing my level 22 Thane and she was playing a level 16 Shaman. 
<br />

<br />
There was a battle going on, a bunch of Albions and Mids were fighting it out and I tried to explain to my wife what was happening. 
<br />

<br />
What does she do? She runs her little Kobold bottom out to the middle of the battle to watch. She even waves at some level 50 Armsman in epic gear (I just taught her how to do emotes).
<br />

<br />
And she was killed.
<br />

<br />
She messaged me a question, "Honey, why did they kill me?"
<br />

<br />
I answered, "Because we are the enemy realm. This is RvR and they try to kill us and we try to kill them."
<br />

<br />
Silence
<br />

<br />
"But I wasn't hurting anyone. Aren't I grey to them?" She asks.
<br />

<br />
I smile as I read the message across my screen, "Yes dear, but someday you will be stronger and will do the same to them."
<br />

<br />
She releases and runs back to sit beside my Thane and rest.
<br />

<br />
"Its not very nice being killed like that." She types.
<br />

<br />
"I know sweety" I reply as I watch the battle from the safety of the frontier keep. Bodies are falling, bolts are flying and the death spam is impressive.
<br />

<br />
"I'm not going to do that when I grow up." She said.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Bless her heart.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
